    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>The Pittsburgh Pirates continued to slash veterans from their roster, releasing catcher MIKE LaVALLIERE yesterday despite owing him $4.05 million over the next two seasons.</p>
        <p>The unexpected move hands the full-time starting job to DON SLAUGHT, who has platooned the last three seasons, and makes light-hitting TOM PRINCE the backup.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>The Pittsburgh Pirates continued to slash veterans from their roster, releasing catcher MIKE LaVALLIERE yesterday despite owing him $4.05 million over the next two seasons.</p>
        <p>The unexpected move hands the full-time starting job to DON SLAUGHT, who has platooned the last three seasons, and makes light-hitting TOM PRINCE the backup.</p>
        <p>If LaValliere isn't claimed on waivers by Thursday, he can cut a deal with any team he chooses. His new team must pay only the major league minimum $109,000 salary, with the Pirates responsible for the rest. (AP)  SPORTS PEOPLE: BASEBALL</p>
      </block>
